value.string: A single story residence with sunset views and located close to parks, beaches and Lahaina Town. This 4 bed 2 bath cinder block home has a 2 bed 2 bath detached Ohana with rental income potential or for family and guest while visiting on island. Upgrades include Star Energy Saver windows and doors, hard wood Pergo flooring, new carpet in bedrooms, Marble tile flooring and new cabinets in kitchen and counter tops in kitchen and baths, composite shingle 50 year roof and paint. New solar water heater and an attic exhaust fan has been installed to cool entire house down. Ceiling fans throughout with termite resistant Redwood interior walls. Mango and Papaya trees on property with the most delicious fruits to enjoy. Sold unfurnished but all appliances are included in sale. New septic tank installed for Ohana. Buyer is to do own due diligence as some improvements to Ohana are not to county code.

Looking for peace and tranquility with a stunning ocean view, too? Drive down a little country lane that takes you to the macadamia nut orchard, then to the private home which faces the expansive, green pasture and north shore view beyond. This home recently underwent extensive remodeling which included a 500+ square foot addition, new bathroom, new septic system; all fully permitted. Seller may consider financing with significant down payment. Tenant occupied - need 48 hours notice to show.

A must see! This custom built three bedroom, two and a half bath home comes with a bright and expansive open floor plan for family and entertaining. Located in the Alii Village subdivision which is centrally located to shopping, dining, schools, a few blocks from the beach and the Kihei Aquatic center. This architectural designed home boasts over 2,500 sqft of living area plus a fully-fenced backyard with a covered lanai, that is perfect for outdoor entertaining. Some features include: Central A/C, gas Wolf stove, and Frigidaire/Fisher Paykel/Kenmore Elite appliances, a large walk-in closet with built in cabinets in the master bedroom, a walk-in pantry, laundry room, and an oversized garage!

INCREDIBLE VALUE HERE! Location! Location! Location! Quick stroll to Kamaole Beach One (see photos #8 and 18 - ) Also easy access to surfing, terrific shopping and excellent restaurants. An elementary school is close by but not too close to hear the children enjoying life! The home itself is a good size and can be utilized as either a four or five bedroom home. The living room opens to a covered lanai with ocean and Haleakala views. The gardens are privately tucked away for privacy. This lot has potential for an ohana. Enjoy a wonderful Hawaiian lifestyle in this great neighborhood. This location is across from a nice park area. Presently rented month to month. This is definitely South Maui's Best Buy!

A premier community located above Kamaole 1 Beach Park. This comfortable, single story home has mahogany wood floors and remodeled bathrooms. It is rare to find a 4 bedroom single story home and this is a great subdivision to call home. Backyard has a water feature for some tropical ambiance.

Rarely available oceanfront property on bluff overlooking Hana Bay. Within easy walking distance to swimming, shopping, and the Hotel Hana Maui. Owned by the same kama'aina faimily since 1924. The property includes an older vacant home.

This very spacious home is located in Kahana area, in walking distance to sandy beach. Very private and very quiet setting, with a large yard and large upstairs deck. With a very versatile floor plan, this is the perfect family home, vacation home or investment opportunity. This home is not part of a subdivision and there is no homeowners' association.

Incredible West facing ocean views from this property located within walking distance to Sugar Beach. Custom built home has granite counter top upgrades, tile flooring, well appointed upstairs lanai for enjoying the beautiful ocean at sunset. Garage has 12' ceilings. Guest bedroom downstairs is fully appointed with own bath and 9' ceilings. A/C in all rooms. Large driveway for boat and parking. Detached Ohana with carport, 1 bd/1 ba, own laundry. Large garage / shop extensive ornamental rock walls give a nice feel to this custom built home. Just 15 minutes to a variety of services and beaches on South Maui. Close to windsurf and kite surf beaches on the North Shore. The sellers are also open to a lease option to purchase the home.

Delightful, peaceful upcountry like setting, just minutes from Wailuku town all the central Maui amenities. This 4 Bedroom - 4 Bath, single story home has 2,320 s.f. of living space on 1 full acre of Agricultural zoned land. Located at 177 Malaihi Road, boasting majestic West Maui mountain views. Versatile floor plan includes; two main entrances with two family rooms, laminate wood flooring, tile bathrooms and carpeted bedrooms. There are two water meters; one county and one private ag water.

Live the South Maui lifestyle in this beautiful home and cottage. Ke Ali'i Kai is one of the most sought after neighborhoods in South Maui and central to Kamaole Beach I, restaurants, shopping and just minutes away from Wailea golf courses and scuba diving. Upgraded bamboo flooring, a 2-car garage with additional parking, solar water, sky tubes that allow natural light in the living room, rock wall, low-maintenance yard and brick courtyard distinguish this home. Both homes currently rented with tenants on month-to-month leases. $80 per month HOA fees include refuse, common area maintenance and reserves. See Lot 88 on final photo for position within neighborhood.

What a great opportunity to live off the land and be self sustainable. Over 13 lush usable acres with varied terrain including 2 ponds, valleys and high ground with ocean views. Many great building sites. Permitted structures and other improvements. Many mature fruit trees and tropical flowers to provide income and food for some energetic farmers. Main structure in the process of being converted into a dwelling. Located ocean-side of Hana Highway. Showings will require some time, so be prepared to spend at least a half hour or more...

Lovely home in desirable Kahana Ridge. Relax and enjoy the ocean views from the cozy front lanai. Open plan design with high ceiling in the living/dining areas. The kitchen features wood cabinets, island with storage, breakfast bar along with tiled back splash, double sink and walk in pantry. Wood flooring throughout main areas of the home and carpet in the bedrooms. Split entry floorplan gives the main living area up with master suite privacy. The master suite has a jacuzzi tub, separate shower, walk in closet and a vanity with generous storage. There are 2 bedrooms, a family room with built ins and full bath down along with the entry to the lanai leading to the hot tub surrounded by tropical plantings in a private fenced yard. Short Sale. Seller holds active Real Estate License.

Quiet Location in a Quaint residential area, just a very short walk down a charming street to Wailuku town. Built in 2006 with a fabulous gourmet kitchen and high end appliances. This spacious home has vaulted ceilings and even boasts wonderful ocean and mountain views. The 5 bedrooms and 4 baths are currently is being used as 3 separate living areas 3/2.5, 1/1 & 1/1 perfect for an extended family. A must see! Call today for a private showing.

Located in Kulamanu "Gathering place For Birds." Upcountry living. Cool and peaceful with views of the West Maui's, North Shore, Kahakuloa, Ranch and grazing lands. Deer, pheasant and cows in your back ground. Views of the island of Lanai and majestic Haleakala. This 3 bed 2.5 Bath home overlooks a grassy common area and native Hawaiian plants, not others' roof tops. Enjoy the Starry Night skies with the moon's glow and Pueo (Hawaiian owl) soaring in the evening light. This home has a very easy and open feeling on the main floor which opens to one of two covered lanai's. The entry is inviting with Engineered Natural Horizontal Bamboo Flooring and it's creamy feel. The real wood burning Fireplace with circulating fan will keep you toasty during the cool winter evenings.

This is an approved short sale at $749,000. Shoudl the offer be lower than $749,000 it will be subject to bank approval. What a great value! There was a private sale in the neighborhood for $889,000. Beautiful wood floors and nice finishes. Private neighborhood in a gated community and backyard looks at a "jungle" which makes it in the quiet part of the neighborhood! Description may vary from county records. This is a must see! Backup offers are welcome!

This is a corporate owned property. Great opportunity for savy investor. Property needs work and to be sold strictly as is! No sellers disclosure will be provided. Listing Broker and Seller do not warrant or make any representations regarding the reliability and accuracy of any information pertaining to this property. Sold as is, where is. Interested parties are encouraged to perform their own due diligence. For special financing and incentives, contact a local REALTOR.

Welcome to Ocean View Estates in Central Maui. The beauty of the Waiehu coastline is often unappreciated. See the surfers challenge the waves or the natural elegance of the sand dunes. Have breakfast on the huge, enclosed lanai and watch the sun rise over Haleakala. The Waiehu public golf course and the baseball park are close by. This is not a drive-by. The 2nd level shows off a beautiful koa kitchen with stainless steel appliances, custom wood flooring, vaulted ceilings, ample wall space to display your art, the master bedroom and master bath, 2 guest bedrooms and 1 guest bathroom. The 1st level has an entry foyer, family room with lanai, office, enclosed work area, hobby room, laundry center, and 2-car garage. This is not a distressed property and will be sold unfurnished.

Fairway to Heaven is this ocean view, luxury home on the Kaanapali Kai Course in West Maui. This contemporary home boasts 4 bedrooms, 3 baths, 2,630 square feet interior and is situated on a 11,567 square foot parcel with mature landscaping, a fenced and gated pool, and is next to hole number 5 on a PGA golf course. Best of all this home is not only move-in ready but is being sold turn-key, fully furnished and stocked with small appliances, kitchenware, and linens. Front of home has great room and family room with ocean views and 1,215 square foot deck that wraps around from the carport to the pool area. Back of home has golf course and mountain views. Great location is convenient to everything and walking distance to resorts, beach, dining and shopping. Exit backyard to the right and follow golf course to walking bridge that takes you to Kaanapali resorts and Whaler's Village shopping center. Looking to retire or live part time in Hawaii? Fairway to Heaven maybe for you, just pack a suitcase. Want a second home or vacation home with easy access to golf with great weather? Check out this house before someone else scoops it up. This house is designed for natural ventilation, all year-round but comes with two central air conditioner units. Glass sliders provide great natural light and ventilation all over home. Vaulted exposed beams throughout add a spacious feel. Marble and Travertine flooring in the kitchen, baths and bedrooms feel cool underfoot, while rich wood flooring accents the great room with a sunken seating area. Dream floor plan has a separate master suite with a walk-in closet and large master bath with access to backyard. To the left of great room is front entry, family room with a small wet bar with fridge, three bedrooms and two baths. Laundry closet hosts a vintage washer and dryer. Home was built in 1973 and has been remodeled and updated through the years (TMK records show 5 bedrooms and the house now has 4, and a rooftop deck added above the carport also not on records). Current Annual taxes for this house, non-owner occupied, are $4,099.23 a year. Find your little slice of paradise at Fairway to Heaven luxury ocean view home on hole #5 on the Kaanapali Kai golf course: Off the Honoapiilani Highway turn on to Halelo Street, Home is at the end on the left.

Move to cool upcountry Maui where the air is crisp and clean. Concrete block style home with 3 bedrooms 2 baths with a cute kitchen with lots of hardwood cabinets and a long counter for added convenience. Nice dining room area with a wide livingroom great for entertaining. Large picture window offering pastorial views. Cute 2 bedroom 1 bath cottage in a distance offering peace and privacy. An amazing back yard fit for a King and Queen. Incredible fruit bearing trees with green banana bunches, lots of avacados, oranges, mango and macadamia nuts. A private park in your own back yard where the grass is green and you could probably Golf at home. Drive around in a golf cart or bring your truck to the back yard. Several small buildings at the back of the property for added enjoyment.
